  <h1>
   <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Audio/i_Audio_Stop_All_Audio.png"/><br/>
   Stop All Audio
  </h1>
  This action can be used to stop
  <i>
   all
  </i>
  audio that is currently playing (note that even if audio is flagged as paused it will be stopped with this function and you cannot resume it again later).
  <h4>
   Action Syntax:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Audio/a_Audio_Stop_All_Audio.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Audio/e_Audio_Stop_All_Audio.png"/><br/>
  The above action block code checks for a mouse button press and if one is detected it then checks
    a global variable to see if it is not true. If it is not true, then a sound is played and the global variable set to
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  , otherwise all sound is stopped and the global variable is set to
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  .
 </body>
</html>